detailedDescription.articleBody: A cockle is an edible, marine bivalve mollusc. Although many small edible bivalves are loosely called cockles, true cockles are species in the family Cardiidae. True cockles live in sandy, sheltered beaches throughout the world.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Leonurus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Lamiaceae. It is native to Europe and Asia, naturalized in New Zealand, Hawaii, New Caledonia, and much of North and South America.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Broken heart is a metaphor for the intense emotional stress or pain one feels at experiencing great and deep longing. The concept is cross-cultural, often cited with reference to a desired or lost lover.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Braveheart is a 1995 American epic historical fiction war film directed and co-produced by Mel Gibson, who portrays William Wallace, a late-13th-century Scottish warrior.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: ब्रेवहार्ट 1995 की अमेरिकी महाकाव्य ऐतिहासिक फिक्शन वॉर फिल्म है, जिसे मेल गिब्सन द्वारा निर्देशित और सह-निर्मित किया गया है, जो 13 वीं सदी के स्कॉटिश योद्धा, विलियम वालेस का किरदार निभा रहे हैं।
